snippet: Like the wolf in America, the dingo is a symbol that may mean one thing to hunters or sheep ranchers, and another to scientists and nature lovers.
abstract: Dingo, a subspecies of wolf native to Australia, have been the subject of passionate public efforts to both protect and persecute them; human drama became entangled with the enigmatic wild dog over 30 years ago with the death of 9-week old Azaria Chamberlain, whose mother claimed that a dingo had taken the child; Chamberlain case and dingoes themselves are back in the spotlight as the nation awaits the results of a fourth coroner's inquest into the infant's death.

byline.original: By JAMES GORMAN and CHRISTINE KENNEALLY

lead_paragraph: Like the wolf in America, the dingo is a symbol that may mean one thing to hunters or sheep ranchers, and another to scientists and nature lovers.

headline.seo: Australia’s View of the Dingo Evolves
headline.main: Australia’s Changing View of the Dingo
headline.print_headline: Australia’s Changing View of the Dingo
